Advanced Tool Management Macros
Advanced Tool Management (ATM) can use macros to obsolete a tool within a tool group.
Macros 8001 to 8200 represent tools 1 through 200. You can set one of these macros to 1
to expire a tool. For example:
= 1 (this expires tool 1)
8001
= 0 (this makes tool 1 available)
